{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Full screen windows enable people to focus on the task at hand by removing extra system UI and deferring to more of the content they care about. OS X 10.11 adds new flexibility to how these full screen windows can be configured and controlled. Hear from the experts how to get your Mac app ready to take advantage of this new functionality. Learn key strategies to making your window content be adaptive depending on the space available."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]}]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2015\/221\/","type":"reference"}},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc15-221-improving-the-full-screen-window-experience"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC15"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC15-221-Improving-the-Full-Screen-Window-Experience","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC15","role":"sampleCode","title":"Improving the Full Screen Window Experience","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"references":{"WWDC15.jpeg":{"type":"image","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC15.jpeg","traits":["1x","l